3cd-0197829588e6","name":"Beta-carotene","unit":"mcg","amount":450,"foodId":null,"source":"admin","itemType":"supplement","sourceUrl":null,"confidence":"high","nutrientId":null,"sourceText":null,"servingLabel":null,"supplementId":"c03be7e3-33d2-5d0c-8257-cde605b5ab1e","normalizedName":"beta_carotene"},{"id":"1e0a35c0-f0cb-4ac3-940f-e2a49a365112","name":"Vitamin D3","unit":"mcg","amount":5,"foodId":null,"source":"admin","itemType":"supplement","sourceUrl":null,"confidence":"high","nutrientId":null,"sourceText":null,"servingLabel":null,"supplementId":"927083fb-b90a-5a24-b4c5-5067b06ead5f","normalizedName":"vitamin_d3"}]'::jsonb, '{"dosage":"for use. Read the","locale":"en","parser":"blackmores_structured_ingredients_v2","titleEn":"Blackmores Superkids™ Immune Chewables","htmlLength":166146,"validation":{"status":"pass","reasons":[],"summary":"5 matchable canonical facts.","checkedAt":"2026-05-21T13:09:48.620Z","matchableFactCount":5},"description":"A great-tasting natural citrus flavoured supplement to support kids’ immune health. Contains zinc, vitamins C, D & E with no added sugar and supports general","descriptionEn":"A great-tasting natural citrus flavoured supplement to support kids’ immune health. Contains zinc, vitamins C, D & E with no added sugar and supports general","descriptionTh":null,"extractedText":"Superkids™ Immune Chewables All Products Shop All Products New Products Best Sellers Vegan Certified Women&#x27;s Health Men&#x27;s Health Kid&#x27;s Health Infant & Toddler Nutrition By Category Arthritis, Joint & Bone Brain & Cognitive Health Cold, Flu & Immunity Digestive & Gut Health Energy Everyday Health Eye Health Fish & Nutritional Oils Heart Health Infant & Toddler Nutrition Kids&#x27; Health Men&#x27;s Health Multivitamins Muscle Support Nails, Hair & Skin Preconception, Pregnancy & Breastfeeding Stress Relief & Sleep Support Women&#x27;s Health By Ingredient Calcium CoQ10 Curcumin Echinacea Fish Oil & Omega 3 Glucosamine Iron Magnesium Probiotics Selenium Vitamin B Vitamin C Vitamin D Vitamin E Zinc Health Hub By Categories By Type Latest Articles Action Plans Arthritis, Bone & Joint Beauty & Skincare Brain & Cognitive Health Cold, Flu & Immunity Digestive & Gut Health Energy Everyday Health Eye Health Fish & Nutrition Oils Heart & Cardiovascular Health Kids & Infant Health Men&#x27;s Health Muscle Support & Fitness Preconception, Pregnancy & Breastfeeding Recipes Stress Relief & Sleep Support Women&#x27;s Health Action Plans Articles Recipes Latest Articles About Blackmores About Blackmores Our Heritage Our Approach Our Impact Our Sustainability Pillars Our People & Culture Our Careers Our Ambassadors & Partners Contact us Ask A Naturopath Our Newsroom Blackmores Subscribe Search Home Chevron Icon Horizontal products Chevron Icon Horizontal Blackmores Superkids™ Immune Chewables Size Size 60 capsules Support your child’s daily wellbeing with BLACKMORES Superkids Immune Chewables, these delicious citrus-flavoured tablets deliver antioxidants to reduce free radicals formed in the body. This chewable formula helps maintain immune system health and support general health and wellbeing. It’s a delicious way to help support kids’ daily wellbeing, it contain ingredients such as zinc and vitamins C, D & E that assist healthy growth and development. Good health changes everything—support your child’s immune system with BLACKMORES Superkids Immune Chewables. Product Format Chewable Tablet Always read the label and follow the directions for use. Read the warnings before purchase. Support For Kids Health Immune System Health General Health No Added Yeast No Added Gluten No Added Wheat No Added Dairy Benefits & How To Use Benefits Contains 4 essential nutrients to help support kids&#x27; immune system function: Zinc is a factor in the maintenance of general wellbeing and helps to support normal immune function. Vitamin C ascorbic acid which is known for its role normal functioning of the immune system. Vitamin C is widely found in fruits and vegetables. Good sources include blackcurrants, guava, citrus and kiwi fruit and vegetables such as broccoli, capsicum and sprouts. However, research undertaken in 2014-15 found that only one in twenty (5.1%) of Australian children were meeting the minimum number of serves of fruit and vegetables each day*. Vitamin D contributes to normal function of the immune system and is found in a limited range of foods. Vitamin D contributes to normal function of the immune system which can be found in a limited range of foods and produced from skin exposure to sunlight. Vitamin E is required for normal immune system function and Beta carotene (pro vitamin A) directly and indirectly supports immune function. *http://www.abs.gov.au/ausstats Dosage Children 2-12 years Chew (do not swallow whole) 1 tablet once a day, or as prescribed by a health professional. Take with food. Use only under adult supervision. Not recommended for children under 2 years. Warnings Always read the label and follow the directions for use. KEEP OUT OF REACH OF CHILDREN. Vitamin supplements should not replace a balanced diet. Excess consumption may have a laxative effect If you have any pre-existing conditions or are on any medications always talk to your health professional before use. Some products should be ceased at least two weeks before any elective surgery, please confirm with your health professional. Contains soya bean products and sulfites. Benefits Dosage Warnings Contains 4 essential nutrients to help support kids&#x27; immune system function: Zinc is a factor in the maintenance of general wellbeing and helps to support normal immune function. Vitamin C ascorbic acid which is known for its role normal functioning of the immune system. Vitamin C is widely found in fruits and vegetables. Good sources include blackcurrants, guava, citrus and kiwi fruit and vegetables such as broccoli, capsicum and sprouts. However, research undertaken in 2014-15 found that only one in twenty (5.1%) of Australian children were meeting the minimum number of serves of fruit and vegetables each day*. Vitamin D contributes to normal function of the immune system and is found in a limited range of foods. Vitamin D contributes to normal function of the immune system which can be found in a limited range of foods and produced from skin exposure to sunlight. Vitamin E is required for normal immune system function and Beta carotene (pro vitamin A) directly and indirectly supports immune function. *http://www.abs.gov.au/ausstats Children 2-12 years Chew (do not swallow whole) 1 tablet once a day, or as prescribed by a health professional. Take with food. Use only under adult supervision. Not recommended for children under 2 years. Always read the label and follow the directions for use. KEEP OUT OF REACH OF CHILDREN. Vitamin supplements should not replace a balanced diet. Excess consumption may have a laxative effect If you have any pre-existing conditions or are on any medications always talk to your health professional before use. Some products should be ceased at least two weeks before any elective surgery, please confirm with your health professional. Contains soya bean products and sulfites. Ingredients Active ingredients per chewable tablet: d-alpha-tocopheryl acid succinate 5.8 mg equivalent vitamin E 7 IU Zinc citrate dihydrate 9.3 mg equivalent dihydrate zinc 3 mg Calcium ascorbate dihydrate 99.4 mg equivalent ascorbic acid (vitamin C) 82.2 mg Betacarotene 450 micrograms Colecalciferol 5 micrograms equivalent vitamin D3 200 IU Superkids™ Immune Chewables Reviews Let&#x27;s stay in touch Instagram Facebook TikTok LinkedIn Back To Top About Blackmores About Blackmores Our Heritage Our Approach Our Impact Our Sustainability Approach Our People & Culture Our Careers Our Ambassadors & Partners Our Newsroom About Blackmores About Blackmores Our Heritage Our Approach Our Impact Our Sustainability Approach Our People & Culture Our Careers Our Ambassadors & Par