o anticipate consumer demand. Backed by science Premium quality formula 50+ year heritage Certified B-Corp We are B-Corp Certified B Corps are for-profit companies that meet high standards of social and environmental performance, transparency, and accountability. Swisse is a brand of H&H Group, a certified B Corp. We feel honoured to be part of a global community using business as a force for good. Frequently Asked Questions Do we need to take vitamin supplements? The key is to ensure that we get a complete and balanced intake of nutrients each day. However, due to lifestyle limitations and dietary choices, we may not always receive the necessary nutrients in adequate amounts. In such cases, dietary supplements can be beneficial. Can Swisse products be taken alongside medication or medical treatments? Each individual has different nutritional and medicinal needs. If you are unsure whether Swisse products are suitable for you, it is best to consult a doctor. Please note that dietary supplements do not prevent, alter, or replace medical treatment or a well-balanced diet. What is the best time to take vitamins? Some supplements work best when taken with food, while others are more effective on an empty stomach. It is essential to follow the instructions on the label to maximize the benefits of each product. How long do dietary supplements last? In general, dietary supplements have a shelf life of approximately two years from the manufacturing date. Where does Swisse source its ingredients? We carefully select and source high-quality, premium-grade ingredients from around the world to ensure that only the best components go into our products. Where are Swisse products manufactured? Most of our products are manufactured in Australia. Please refer to the product packaging for the specific country of origin. The recommended dosage on the label applies to which age group? The recommended dosage is intended for individuals aged 18 and above. You may also like Swisse C Acerol