Wheat Benefits & How To Use Benefits Supports memory recall. Maintains cognitive function including learning, memory and attention. Maintains healthy blood circulation. Contains a standardised extract of ginkgo biloba. Dosage Adults Take 1 tablet three times a day, or as prescribed by a health professional. Take with food. Warnings Always read the label and follow directions for use. Do not use during pregnancy or breastfeeding. If you have pre-existing bleeding disorders, epilepsy, heart conditions; or if taking blood thinner medication like warfarin, talk to your doctor before use. If symptoms persist, talk to your health professional. If you have any pre-existing conditions or are on any medications always talk to your healthcare professional before use. Some products should be ceased at least two weeks before any elective surgery, please confirm with your health professional. Contains soya bean products. Benefits Dosage Warnings Supports memory recall. Maintains cognitive function including learning, memory and attention. Maintains healthy blood circulation. Contains a standardised extract of ginkgo biloba. Adults Take 1 tablet three times a day, or as prescribed by a health professional. Take with food. Always read the label and follow directions for use. Do not use during pregnancy or breastfeeding. If you have pre-existing bleeding disorders, epilepsy, heart conditions; or if taking blood thinner medication like warfarin, talk to your doctor before use. If symptoms persist, talk to your health professional. If you have any pre-existing conditions or are on any medications always talk to your healthcare professional before use. Some products should be ceased at least two weeks before any elective surgery, please confirm with your health professional. Contains soya bean products. The Blackmores Difference Ingredients Active ingredients per tablet: Ginkgo biloba (gingko) extract dry conc. 40 mg equivalent dry leaf 2000 mg (2 g) standardised to ginkgo flavonglyco