usy and active lifestyle. - Riboflavin contributes to the normal function of the nervous system - Vitamin B6 contributes to normal energy-yielding metabolism. - Vitamin B12 contributes to normal function of the brain and nervous system - Vitamin C and E Contributes to the protection of cells from oxidative stress - Vitamin D contributes to normal blood calcium levels. - Vitamin D contributes to the maintenance of normal bones. - Vitamin D contributes to the maintenance of normal teeth. - Zinc contributes to the maintenance of normal hair - Folic acid/Folate contributes to normal red blood formation - Selenium contributes to the protection of cells from oxidative stress.","validation":{"status":"needs_review","reasons":["no_dosed_facts"],"summary":"No usable per-serving product facts.","checkedAt":"2026-05-21T10:12:53.818Z","matchableFactCount":0},"description":"Stay energized and active with Essential Multivitamin by Swisse. Perfect for busy lifestyles in Thailand.","priceAmount":990,"descriptionEn":"Stay energized and active with Essential Multivitamin by Swisse. Perfect for busy lifestyles in Thailand.","descriptionTh":"อยู่กระฉับกระเฉงและกระตือรือร้นด้วย Essential Multivitamin จาก Swisse เหมาะสำหรับไลฟ์สไตล์ที่วุ่นวายในประเทศไทย","extractedText":"Swisse Essential Multivitamin - Swisse Thailand Skip to content Products Back Products Beauty Eye Care Gummies Gut Health Immunity Joints, Bones, & Muscles Moisturisers Multivitamins Serums Skin Super Fruits & Herbs All Products Range Wellness Beauty Skincare About Back Our Story Ingredients Wellness Hub Sign in Search Cart (0) Cart empty Your cart is empty Continue shopping     svg]:w-full group-hover:text-uiGrey\"> Home / Essential Multivitamin   Skip to product information Open media 1 in modal Open media 2 in modal Open media 3 in modal Open media 4 in modal Swisse Ultivite Essential Multivitamin SWISSE ULTIVITE ESSENTIAL MULTIVITAMIN is a quality formula containing 22 vitamins, minerals, antioxidants and herbs. It’s tailored to support energy production, relieve fatigue and help prevent Vitamin B12 dietary deficiencies. Swisse committed to contributing positively to the needs of society and the planet, and we are the carbon neutral company. #Number1MultivitaminBrandfromAustralia Sale price 990 ฿ Where to buy Buy at TikTok Buy at Shopee Buy at Lazada Buy at Line Benefits Formulated based on scientific evidence to provide nutritional support for a busy and active lifestyle. - Riboflavin contributes to the normal function of the nervous system - Vitamin B6 contributes to normal energy-yielding metabolism. - Vitamin B12 contributes to normal function of the brain and nervous system - Vitamin C and E Contributes to the protection of cells from oxidative stress - Vitamin D contributes to normal blood calcium levels. - Vitamin D contributes to the maintenance of normal bones. - Vitamin D contributes to the maintenance of normal teeth. - Zinc contributes to the maintenance of normal hair - Folic acid/Folate contributes to normal red blood formation - Selenium contributes to the protection of cells from oxidative stress. Key Ingredients Each tablet contains 22 active ingredients with 13 types of vitamins, 7 minerals and 2 natural extracts, including: - Completed B vitamins from 1-12 - Calcium and Vitamin D - Vitamin C & E, Zinc, Selenium - Ferrous & Folic acid - Beta Carotene & Lutein - L-lysine essential amino acid - Extract of Shiitake Mushroom, Grapeseed Directions and Warnings DIRECTIONS: 1 tablet daily. Take during or immediately after a meal, or as directed by a healthcare professional.  WARNINGS: Children, pregnant women, and patient with kidney stones should not consume. Should eat a variety of the five categories of food in appropriate proportions STORAGE: Store below 25C, in a cool, dry place. Do not use, if cap seal is broken Reasons to love us We have been developing science-based formulas using premium ingredients sourced from around the world for over 50 years. We believe in natural ingredients being our hero ingredients. We also pursue the latest research findings to formulate our advanced product ranges and consistently strive to anticipate consumer demand. Backed by science Premium quality formula 50+ year heritage Certified B-Corp We are B-Corp Certified B Corps are for-profit companies that meet high standards of social and environmental performance, transparency, and accountability. Swisse is a brand of H&H Group, a certified B Corp. We feel honoured to be part of a global community using business as a force for good. Frequently Asked Questions What are the benefits of multivitamins? Multivitamins help nourish and restore the body from stress-related conditions, such as post-exercise fatigue. They support energy production, enhance strength and mobility, and promote relaxation. High calcium and vitamin D – Support bone and dental health. Vitamin C, Vitamin E, Biotin, Zinc, Nicotinamide, and Selenium – Help maintain healthy hair, skin, and nails. Folic acid and Iron – Support blood health. Beta-Carotene and Lutein – Support eye health. Essential Amino Acid L-Lysine – Contributes to overall well-being Do we need to take vitamin supplements? The key is to ensure that we get a complete and balanced intake of nutrients each day. However, due to lifestyle limitations and dietary choices, we may not always receive the necessary nutrients in adequate amounts. In such cases, dietary supplements can be beneficial. Can Swisse products be taken alongside medication or medical treatments? Each individual has different nutritional and medicinal needs. If you are unsure whether Swisse products are suitable for you, it is best to consult a doctor. Please note that dietary supplements do not prevent, alter, or replace medical treatment or a well-balanced diet. What is the best time to take vitamins? Some supplements work best when taken with food, while others are more effective on an empty stomach. It is essential to follow the instructions on the label to maximize the benefits of each product. How long do dietary supplements last? In general, dietary supplements have a shelf life of approximately two years from the manufacturing date. Where does Swisse source its ingredients? We carefully select and source high-quality, premium-grade ingredients from around the world to ensure that only the best components go into our products. Where are Swisse products manufactured? Most of our products are manufactured in Australia. Please refer to the product packaging for the specific country of origin. The recommended dosage on the label applies to which age group? The recommended dosage is intended for individuals aged 18 and above. You may also like Swisse Ultivite Multivitamin with B Vitamins Sale price 650 ฿ Swisse Ultivite Multivitamin with Folic Acid Sale price 650 ฿ Our Products Beauty Eye Care Gut Health Gummies Immunity Joints, Bones, & Muscles Multivitamins Super Fruits & Herbs Skincare About Swisse Our Story Ingredients Help & Support FAQs Contact Us Privacy Policy Follow Us &copy; Swisse Thailand , 2026 Choosing a selection results in a full page refresh.\n\nBenefits Formulated based on scientific evidence to provide nutritional support for a busy and active lifestyle. - Riboflavin contributes to the normal function of the nervous system - Vitamin B6 contributes to normal energy-yielding metabolism. - Vitamin B12 contributes to normal function of the brain and nervous system - Vitamin C and E Contributes to the protection of cells from oxidative stress - Vitamin D contributes to normal blood calcium levels. - Vitamin D contributes to the maintenance of normal bones. - Vitamin D contributes to the maintenance of normal teeth. - Zinc contributes to the maintenance of normal hair - Folic acid/Folate contributes to normal red blood formation - Selenium contributes to the protection of cells from oxidative stress.\n\nKey Ingredients Each tablet contains 22 active ingredients with 13 types of vitamins, 7 minerals and 2 natural extracts, including: - Completed B vitamins from 1-12 - Calcium and Vitamin D - Vitamin C & E, Zinc, Selenium - Ferrous & Folic acid - Beta Carotene & Lutein - L-lysine essential amino acid - Extract of Shiitake Mushroom, Grapeseed\n\nDirections and Warnings DIRECTIONS: 1 tablet daily. Take during or immediately after a meal, or as directed by a healthcare professional.","productOffers":[{"url":"https://vt.tiktok.com/ZMBa1GBYF/?page=TikTokShop","label":"Buy at TikTok","status":"active","network":"swisse_where_to_buy","linkType":"direct","platform":"tiktok","priority":100},{"url":"https://shopee.co.th/swisse_thailand","label":"Buy at Shopee","status":"active","network":"swisse_where_to_buy","linkType":"direct","platform":"shopee","priority":99},{"url":"https://s.lazada.co.th/s.vPVfK","label":"Buy at Lazada","status":"active","network":"swisse_where_to_buy","linkType":"direct","platform":"lazada","priority":98},{"url":"https://shop.line.me/@swisse","label":"Buy at Line","status":"active","network":"swisse_where_to_buy","linkType":"direct","platform":"line","priority":97},{"url":"https://www.tiktok.com/@swisse_thailand","label":"Where to buy","status":"active","network":"swisse_where_to_buy","linkType":"direct","platform":"tiktok","priority":96}],"productVendor":"Swisse Thailand","keyIngredients":"Each tablet contains 22 active ingredients with 13 types of vitamins, 7 minerals and 2 natural extracts, including: - Completed B vitamins from 1-12 - Calcium and Vitamin D - Vitamin C & E, Zinc, Selenium - Ferrous & Folic acid - Beta Carotene & Lutein - L-lysine essential amino acid - Extract of Shiitake Mushroom, Grapeseed","labelImageUrls":[],"productImportId":"07297ad9-a931-40fd-a377-2fa72764a03e","whereToBuyLinks":[{"url":"https://vt.tiktok.com/ZMBa1GBYF/?page=TikTokShop","label":"Buy at TikTok","status":"active","network":"swisse_where_to_buy","linkType":"direct","platform":"tiktok","priority":100},{"url":"https://shopee.co.th/swisse_thailand","label