 follow the instructions on the label to maximize the benefits of each product. How long do dietary supplements last? In general, dietary supplements have a shelf life of approximately two years from the manufacturing date. Where does Swisse source its ingredients? We carefully select and source high-quality, premium-grade ingredients from around the world to ensure that only the best components go into our products. Where are Swisse products manufactured? Most of our products are manufactured in Australia. Please refer to the product packaging for the specific country of origin. The recommended dosage on the label applies to which age group? The recommended dosage is intended for individuals aged 18 and above. You may also like Swisse Ultivite Multivitamin with B Vitamins Sale price 650 ฿ Swisse Ultivite Multivitamin with Folic Acid Sale price 650 ฿ Our Products Beauty Eye Care Gut Health Gummies Immunity Joints, Bones, & Muscles Multivitamins Super Fruits & Herbs Skincare About Swisse Our Story Ingredients Help & Support FAQs Contact Us Privacy Policy Follow Us &copy; Swisse Thailand , 2026 Choosing a selection results in a full page refresh.\n\nBenefits Formulated based on scientific evidence to provide nutritional support for a busy and active lifestyle. - Riboflavin contributes to the normal function of the nervous system - Vitamin B6 contributes to normal energy-yielding metabolism. - Vitamin B12 contributes to normal function of the brain and nervous system - Vitamin C and E Contributes to the protection of cells from oxidative stress - Vitamin D contributes to normal blood calcium levels. - Vitamin D contributes to the maintenance of normal bones. - Vitamin D contributes to the maintenance of normal teeth. - Zinc contributes to the maintenance of normal hair - Folic acid/Folate contributes to normal red blood formation - Selenium contributes to the protection of cells from oxidative stress.\n\nKey Ingredients Each tablet contains 22 active ingredients with 1